    <div class="location">
      <h2>Iguazu Falls</h2>
      <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/300x200?text=Iguazu+Falls" alt="Iguazu Falls">
      <p>Experience the breathtaking Iguazu Falls, a UNESCO World Heritage Site. Witness the cascading water rushing over the precipice, creating a mesmerizing spectacle. Hike the trails, take a boat ride, or enjoy a helicopter tour for different perspectives.</p>
      <button onclick="toggleInfo('iguazu')">More Info</button>
      <div id="iguazu" class="more-info">
        <ul>
          <li>Garganta del Diablo (Devil's Throat)</li>
          <li>Upper and Lower Circuits</li>
          <li>Boat Tours</li>
        </ul>
        <p>The best time to visit Iguazu Falls is during the dry season (May-September) for clearer views and less rain.</p>
        <a href="https://www.iguazuargentina.com/" target="_blank">Visit Iguazu Falls Tourism Website</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="location">
      <h2>Bariloche</h2>
      <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/300x200?text=Bariloche" alt="Bariloche">
      <p>Nestled in the heart of the Andes Mountains, Bariloche is a charming city known for its breathtaking scenery, skiing opportunities, and delicious chocolate. Hike the trails, ski the slopes, or simply enjoy the panoramic views.</p>
      <button onclick="toggleInfo('bariloche')">More Info</button>
      <div id="bariloche" class="more-info">
        <ul>
          <li>Cerro Catedral (Ski Resort)</li>
          <li>Nahuel Huapi National Park</li>
          <li>Chocolate Factories</li>
        </ul>
        <p>The best time to visit Bariloche is during the winter (June-August) for skiing and snowboarding, or during the summer (December-February) for hiking and outdoor activities.</p>
        <a href="https://www.bariloche.gov.ar/turismo" target="_blank">Visit Bariloche Tourism Website</a>
